Four
people have died in a car crash on Monday morning on the R71 near Haenertsburg
in the Mopani District. Department
of Trasport spokesperson Mike Maringa said a driver of a VW Polo lost control
and collided head on with an oncoming Opel bakkie. He said
three people from the VW Polo were certified dead on the scene. The
sedan had five passengers and two sustained injuries. A
passenger from the Corsa bakkie died while the driver and another passenger
were rushed to the hospital with serious injuries. Maringa
said preliminary investigation revealed reckless driving was the possible cause
for the accident.Â  Transport and
Community Safety MEC Mavhungu Lerule-Ramakhanya re-iterated a call to motorists
to drive with caution.